            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_204gc' title='Col. 204GC &mdash; HL Deb 14 July 2003 vol 651 c204GC' name='column_204gc' href='#column_204gc' rel='bookmark'>204GC</a>
            dispute in the intervening period, they can use their existing arrangements which include third party arbitration. I remember saying when responding to an amendment that if there was an agreement, generally speaking the Secretary of State would be reluctant to intervene.</p><p>
